@startuml
title Batch B Onboarding, First Success, And Runtime Awareness (2026-03-17)

skinparam backgroundColor transparent
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam defaultTextAlignment left

package "Current Foundations" {
  [OnboardingWizard\n4-step flow] as Wizard
  [SetupProgress\nstate machine] as Setup
  [Clarification surfaces\nInbox / IssueDetail / Rail] as Clarification
  [Workspace routing\nanalysis/implementation/review] as Routing
  [IssueChangeSurface\nworkspace fields] as ChangeSurface
}

package "Reference Patterns" {
  [Interview-first\nonboarding] as RefInterview
  [WorktreeBanner] as RefBanner
}

package "Batch B Target" {
  [Onboarding Profile] as Profile
  [First-success guidance] as Success
  [IssueRuntimeSummary] as Runtime
}

package "Primary UI Surfaces" {
  [IssueDetail] as IssueDetail
  [Inbox] as Inbox
  [Overview / Layout] as Overview
  [Runs] as Runs
  [Changes] as Changes
}

Wizard --> Profile : add pre-profile recommendation
Setup --> Profile : store in metadata
Clarification --> Success : strengthen existing cues
Wizard --> Success : onboarding source issue banner
Routing --> Runtime
ChangeSurface --> Runtime
RefInterview --> Profile
RefBanner --> Runtime

Success --> IssueDetail
Success --> Inbox
Success --> Overview

Runtime --> IssueDetail
Runtime --> Runs
Runtime --> Changes

note bottom of Success
Goal:
"What happens next?"
"Where should I answer?"
"Is PM still structuring?"
end note

note bottom of Runtime
Runtime truth is not hidden infra.
Translate it as:
- shared vs isolated
- analysis / implementation / review
- fresh / reused / dirty resume
end note

@enduml
